# Arabic / Bidi Text Convention — halaqmap

halaqmap is an Arabic-first product. `<html lang="ar" dir="rtl">` and the
global rule `unicode-bidi: plaintext` (in `src/index.css`) handle most
prose elements (`p`, `li`, `h1-h6`, `td`, `th`, `caption`, `blockquote`,
`figcaption`, `summary`, `label`, `span`, `strong`, `em`, …) automatically.
**You almost never need to set `dir` manually.**

## When writing Arabic strings (code / policies / prompts / SQL seeds)

1. **End-of-sentence punctuation only.** Put `:` `،` `.` `؟` at the END of
   the Arabic sentence, never at the start of a translated/literal line.

2. **Isolate English/Latin tokens.** When the string is rendered as plain
   text inside an Arabic paragraph, prefer one of these forms:
   - Wrap with backticks so the platform auto-isolates them as `<code>`:
     `` `B2B` `` or `` `gpt-4o` ``.
   - Or put the English term on its own line.

   ```ts
   // ❌ BAD — neutral chars between Arabic and English will mis-align
   `النموذج B2B: مع إضافة (برونزي، ذهبي، ماسي)`

   // ✅ GOOD — English term isolated as inline code
   'النموذج `B2B`: مع إضافة (برونزي، ذهبي، ماسي)'
   ```

3. **Do not start an Arabic paragraph with a Latin numeral / Markdown
   header marker / hyphen.** Start with a strong Arabic character so
   `unicode-bidi: plaintext` picks RTL as the paragraph base direction.

   ```md
   ❌ ### فهم للمنصة
   ✅ **فهم للمنصة**
   ```

## When rendering dynamic Arabic content

- Most prose elements get bidi-plaintext for free via the `:where()` rule.
- For generated text inside a `<div>` (e.g. chat bubbles, AI replies,
  `whitespace-pre-wrap` containers), add `dir="rtl"` + the
  `chat-arabic-text` class so the explicit RTL base direction is set:

  ```tsx
  <div dir="rtl" className="chat-arabic-text whitespace-pre-wrap …">
    {content}
  </div>
  ```

- For containers that intentionally must NOT bidi-auto (e.g. a tightly
  designed marquee, RTL-locked carousel), opt out with
  `data-bidi="off"` or `className="bidi-off"`.

## When writing AI system prompts that respond in Arabic

Include this clause verbatim near the top of the system prompt so the
model cooperates with the bidi layer:

> اكتب بالعربية الفصيحة الواضحة، اتجاه RTL، علامات الترقيم في نهاية
> الجملة العربية فقط. ضع أي مصطلح إنجليزي بين علامتي \`backtick\` أو على
> سطر مستقل، ولا تخلطه داخل جملة عربية متّصلة. لا تبدأ الفقرة العربية
> برقم لاتيني أو علامة Markdown مثل `###`.

Reference: `api/_lib/marketingCouncilLab.ts` (CONVERSATION_DOCTRINE).
